prend également &laquo;combattant solitaire&quot; ou éléments de jeu en solo. Une personne peut jouer contre une équipe formée par les trois autres joueurs pour le tour. Les tables peuvent tourner au tour suivant, le joueur solo devient une partie de l&#39;équipe et l&#39;un des anciens membres de l&#39;équipe devient le joueur solo.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Et un point à noter: Tarot a été mentionné dans son italiennes provenant du 15ème siècle!</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Buts du jeu</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Prenez autant de figures que possible pour gagner le match.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Obtenez le plus nombreux dans les Bouts trucs gagné que possible.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Le déclarant a pour but de marquer des points le plus grand nombre tel que défini dans le contrat. Les opposants tentent d&#39;empêcher le déclarant d&#39;atteindre sa / son but.</div>\r\n', '0', ''),
(30, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="/webflashgame/assets/flash_game/upload/images/payment_28_logo_90x50.png" style="width: 137px; height: 76px;" /></p>\r\n', 'Boule', '<h3 id="a_3264" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Boule: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			How to play</h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			All details about how to play multiplayer games can be found in the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gametwist.fr/help.asp?id_topic=479&amp;xslPostFix=&amp;id_article=2865" style="color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">general instructions</a>.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			By clicking on the playing field and drawing the mouse back, you can determine the direction and power of the throw. Releasing the mouse button releases the ball.</p>\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Rules</h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Boule can be played by 2 or 3 players in direct competition. The aim of the game is to get your balls closer to the jack than your opponent(s).</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			At the start of the game the playing surface is chosen at random (sand, earth or grass) and the obstacles (such as water and hills) are placed. A player is then selected to throw the jack. If the jack lands too close to the player or out of bounds, the throw must be taken again. If the player fails to make a valid throw three times, the duty of throwing the jack passes to the next player.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			By clicking on the playing field and drawing the mouse back, you can determine the direction and power of the throw. A power bar below the playing field displays the strength of the throw. Ahead of the throw you can also determine the pitch by adjusting the arrow to the bottom left of the playing field. The flight of the throw in accordance with the power and pitch are displayed when taking the throw itself. Releasing the mouse button releases the ball.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Once the jack has been thrown, the next player takes his/her first throw, attempting to get the ball as close to the jack as possible. All of the players must have thrown one ball before the player, who is furthest from the jack must throw again.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The round comes to an end once all of the balls have been thrown. Only the player, whose ball is closest to the jack at the end of the round, scores points. One point is awarded for every ball, which is closer to the jack than any of the opponent&rsquo;s balls.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			The winner of the round throws the jack at the</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<h3 id="a_3264" style="margin: -10px 10px 31px 3px; padding: 45px 0px 4px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-style: italic; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 153, 204); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">\r\n	Boule: Instructions</h3>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 11px 0px 15px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">\r\n	<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			How to play</h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			All details about how to play multiplayer games can be found in the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gametwist.fr/help.asp?id_topic=479&amp;xslPostFix=&amp;id_article=2865" style="color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">general instructions</a>.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			By clicking on the playing field and drawing the mouse back, you can determine the direction and power of the throw. Releasing the mouse button releases the ball.</p>\r\n		<h4 style="margin: 17px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 2px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 153, 204);">\r\n			Rules</h4>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			Boule can be played by 2 or 3 players in direct competition. The aim of the game is to get your balls closer to the jack than your opponent(s).</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			At the start of the game the playing surface is chosen at random (sand, earth or grass) and the obstacles (such as water and hills) are placed. A player is then selected to throw the jack. If the jack lands too close to the player or out of bounds, the throw must be taken again. If the player fails to make a valid throw three times, the duty of throwing the jack passes to the next player.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 17px; padding: 0px;">\r\n			By clicking on the playing field and drawing the mouse back, you can determine the direction and power of the throw. A power bar below the playing field displays the strength of the throw. Ahead of the throw you can also determine the pitch by adjusting the arrow to the bottom left of the playing field. The flight of the throw in accordance with the power and pitch are displayed when taking the throw itself. Releasing the mouse button releases the ball.</p>\r\n		<p style="margin: 0px 0px